        <abstract> 
<p>GCW has correctly expressed CD’s views when he says he intentionally left the question of the origin of life uncanvassed as being altogether <hi rend="italic">ultra vires</hi> in the present state of our knowledge. Thinks he may somewhere have said that principle of continuity renders it possible that the principle of life will be shown to be a part of, or consequence of, some general law.</p> 
